Yes — you caught the right issue. The bundle host path should be extracted_isos/, not a hardcoded host path like /iso.

The clean pattern is:

Host / bundle path:
  /path/to/aerolit_bundle/extracted_isos
Container internal path:
  /iso

So the container still uses /iso internally because that is simple and stable, but the Quadlet/role bind-mounts your real bundle path into the container:

/path/to/bundle/extracted_isos:/iso:ro,Z

That means the generator can always scan /iso, while the Ansible role can point /iso at whatever bundle got extracted.

